LinkedIn has become Geodemographic database marketers' paradiseIn a plain language, database marketing is a marketing technique that utilizes customer databases.Before the advent of social media platforms like LinkedIn, database marketing was a form of one-to-one direct marketing in which databases of customers (or potential customers) are used to generate personalized communications in promoting products or services to them by targeting geographic locations with their highest concentrations.Windhoek, Namibia.B2B database marketing method that will be discussed in this eBook will allow you to leverage BIG databases like LinkedIn to be reaching B2B companies ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD with personalized and targeted campaigns. In the long run, this should cut down your cost of B2B lead acquisitions for example, list of CEOs of B2B companies from +$10 per lead to almost ZERO AND/OR FREE.Why LinkedIn?LinkedIn has grown into a community of +500 million of B2B owners, professionals, academic experts, young university graduates, coaches and trainers, network marketers, authors, publishers, etc, who have identified themselves by their basic Geodemographic characteristics: - who they are, where they stay (Geography), where they work (company), what they do (job function), job entry and current positions, what interests them, what skills they have, their experience, what education they have received, their voluntary experience, etc.Whether you love or hate the platform, it has become a "paradise" for job seekers, recruiters, network marketers, coaches and trainers, motivational speakers, etc. People are making connections by the seconds on the platform. 80% of B2B social media leads now comes from LinkedIn. The average LinkedIn user spends 17 minutes on the site per month.If you are not looking for job directly, but you want to find new customers or opportunities for your products and services, a huge LinkedIn connections of B2B owners is a must; more so, if you have automated software that you can be using to segment people in your connections into different niche markets by their Geodemographic characteristics ( case studies of how to be doing this are explained inside the eBook with real life examples - get the eBook if you can).Need for an eBook on Geodemographic Database Marketing using LinkedInThe business concept of LinkedIn is very simple.If you are going to get a job or sell anything or ask for funding from LinkedIn members (using LinkedIn platform and its communication tools), you should bring your own list of potential clientele in the profession(s) or field(s) of your interests; and use their LinkedIn business tools to be showcasing what you have to offer; and /or how your expertise can help professionals on the platform grow their businesses and make profits. This is what modern Database Marketing is all about.When you segment and target potential customers on a database by some Geodemographic characteristics such as country, region/province, city, zip code, email, telephone, age, sex, position, occupation, industry, interest, etc., then it is called Geodemographic database marketing.If you do not have your own Geodemographic database of your clients, you can use LinkedIn’s infrastructure and their existing database of employers, decision makers, managers and businesses owners in your niche market to locate them, and start conversations with them (using email, blog, and other messaging tools available on the platform). Such conversations can initially centered on why they should employ you because of your skills; or why they should fund your idea, innovation, businesses or causes. Challenges faced by many LinkedIn membersFinding the right employers or people of the same interest to help to raise funding for anything however, is a big challenge for many LinkedIn members simply because they are not trained on how to be using the platform for fund raising. If you already have Geodemographic database from your niche market that you want to be targeting, and you have good skills to be bringing them into LinkedIn as contacts of potential fund raisers, you can use LinkedIn tools to find them faster than when you have nothing before you joined LinkedIn to start fund raising. This is called Bring You Own Data (BYOD) a principle upon which modern social media like Facebook uses to store millions and even billions of records of people.To succeed on LinkedIn therefore, initially you must forget about posting or blogging about your skills or fund raising projects, but concentrate on bringing your own database of potential clients, employers or fund raisers to join your network.   A great deal of the eBook is focused on how to be acquiring Big (millions) of unstructured databases of B2b owners from WHOIS RECORDS as primary source of potential clients to be invited to join your LinkedIn network. You will learn how to be working with raw and unstructured WHOIS records, cleaning and verifying them, before bringing them into LinkedIn platform for  a one-on-one business engagements as shown below. The eBook will help to solve many challenges faced by LinkedIn members99% of people signing up for LinkedIn account do not have their own databases of potential employers or buyers or fund raisers; and/or the skills to use LinkedIn infrastructure to find the right employers, buyers or fund raisers in their niche markets. Statistics released by Statista in 2016, shows that only 1% of LinkedIn members have on average +10,000 connections or followers.Most people on LinkedIn make the following excuses as to why the number of their LinkedIn connections don't grow.1. I don't know how.2. I don't have the time.3. I don't have the money.4. I don't have a mentor.5. I don't even know where to start.6. I don't see value in +500 connectionThus, having a published eBook and accompanying resource web site that teaches people how to leverage LinkedIn for fund raising for example, will be a hit, and a relief for millions of LinkedIn members who comes to  LinkedIn searching for new job openings, or new opportunities or partners to help them to raise funding for anything.The eBook will cover the following broad areas:
Introduction to using LinkedIn to raise funding for anything;
Optimization of LinkedIn Profile page to raise funding;
Geodemographic database marketing using LinkedIn;
Marketing your crowd funding project to your niche B2B owners on LinkedIn;
Automating LinkedIn business process with 678LinkedIn-GeoMiner software;
Email marketing targeting your 1st, 2nd and 3rd LinkedIn connections;
Best ways to blog and publish about your crowd funding ideas on LinkedIn;
Case studies of using LinkedIn and Geodemographic segmentation for crowd funding;
Whether you already have a LinkedIn account or need to set up a new one, based on my experience in both Geodemographic database marketing and in growing my LinkedIn connections to +16,000, the eBook will teach you the best LinkedIn database marketing practices to be deploying in order to effectively target the right people who are already using the platform for B2B networking.In today’s life of social media “your net worth isn't what you own but who you know, and how many people you know that can help you realize your dream.” The more people you know that can help you in whatever you are doing, the more easily for you to reaching your goal. It is a number's game. About myself and experience in using LinkedIn -  I am among the 1% Supper connector on LinkedInI have been using B2B Geodemographic email databases to build my LinkedIn connections for more the ten months now since September of 2016. By applying my skills in Geodemographic database marketing, my LinkedIn connections has skyrocketed to  over +16,000. This was how I become part of the 1% super connectors of LinkedIn. This was done relatively in a short period since building such huge list of B2B owners and professionals has taken many people years and huge amount of money to complete.My success lies in my ability to fuse in Big Geodemographic Data Mining tactics into my LinkedIn invitation to connect process.For Geo-targeting or marketing of anything, LinkedIn is an amazing platform/tool if you know what you are doing, especially if you know how to use it correctly, not just for job searching for employers or hiring prospective employees, but for fund raising too. It has potential to open doors to multiple opportunities and prospective clientele that you can be engaging to do crowd funding for different causes.This is why I decided to write the eBook about how this can be done primarily for the benefits of those who have great skills or innovative ideas but are finding it difficult to get hired or raise enough money to promote their ideas to the right people (Geodemographic groups) on LinkedIn.This  unique method of crowd funding using Geodemographic database marketing that I will discussed inside the eBook are not well known in general among online marketers, and particularly, among LinkedIn users. This is simply because, it involves first acquisitions of huge email databases of B2B owners/decision-makers who are already on LinkedIn, and are interested in new opportunities including new ways to source funding for their businesses or ideas. This is then followed by inviting them to join your LinkedIn network in order for them to learn how you are using LinkedIn to do crowd funding for yourself or for other people; and how you can help them to raise funding for their own projects or needs.......effect of weak job market around the world makes the eBook a must have for those using LinkedIn to search for new opportunities or new sources of funding.Due to weak job markets across the world, many people rushing to LinkedIn to seek for new opportunities or decent jobs often get easily frustrated and give up too quickly, not because their skills are not in demand, but because many of them are not trained on how to leverage LinkedIn to find their dream jobs or new opportunities, or find the right people that can helped them raise funding for their innovative ideas.....the truth is that 80% of B2B professionals in the world, and people that matters who can take decision about whether to employ you, or help you to source funding from other people for your project(s) or business or innovation  are on LinkedIn.Therefore, if you have innovative business idea or product you want to crowd fund, do not be too shy or timid to ask LinkedIn members to help you out. This is because most of them are successful professionals from various fields, some are business owners, CEOs, managers, etc. Many people that I have come in contact with on LinkedIn are very kind and ready to offer help to those who asked.  Many of them too can easily path with few couple of dollars to even 1000s of dollars to support your fund raising drives if you have good business concept provided you are able to pitch them to fund you. Benefits of the eBookThe eBook will be of benefits to many people.
Anyone in need of funding for anything and want to be targeting 80% of B2B owners that are already on LinkedIn;
Unemployed youths looking to attract the right B2B owners on LinkedIn to partner with to raise funding for their innovative startup ideas.
Pensioners, retiring seniors, CEOs, MDs, and anyone nearing the age of retirement but will need funding to start self-employment project.
Students and parents who will want to pay off their study loans or school fees before they graduate from colleges and universities
Digital marketers who takes on roles and responsibilities of marketing fund raising projects on behalf of their clients
Cost of bringing the entire project to lifeAfter many days of careful planning on how to deliver the eBook and organize various resources that readers of the eBook might need, I am now nearing completion of it, and before long the eBook will be ready for consumption (estimated time for delivery is November/December 2017).I have decided to be in total control of the project, self-publish eBook, page-turning eBook, pdf and epub format for public download and available via:
online landing pages for a small fee if they want only the eBook , or
pay monthly subscription fee if they want to be trained and have access to use tons of associated resources that I will make available via a protected member only site including my +16k LinkedIn connections to start with;

millions of B2B contacts who are likely to be on LinkedIn to connect with,
automated Geodemographic data miner software for LinkedIn and
video tutorials on how to use the eBook, tools and software discussed inside.
Members can use the resources over and over again for different crowd funding projects once they gain access to my protected area.I have the knowledge of how to acquire and market to Big Email Databases of B2B. I also have the ability to write clearly, and as well as the drive to make this an amazing "how-to-raise funding on LinkedIn" eBook for use by anyone that joins my LinkedIn connections.Inside the eBook, I will teach readers all my tricks and help them grow their LinkedIn connections to +15,000 like a pro within matters of months.  Throughout the eBook, I will divulge the tricks of how to be legally asking millions of B2B owners to fund your projects while at the same time you are inviting them to connect with you on LinkedIn. You will not learn this simple secret from anywhere except from me.You will also have one of the best third party LinkedIn business automating tool, which will enable you to be asking  2nd and 3rd degree connections to be raising fund for your projects, businesses, innovative idea or even to paying off your study loan. What I need & what you getI will be fronting all the costs, eBook design, stunning online web page (Landing Page), hosting, and affiliate software. I need your help with this part. It will cost about $15,000 to bring the entire project to life, I need some upfront capital to make this happen.You can order the eBook  upfront as a perk. You will also be able to pay for a 1 year access to download all the associated resources like +20million database of B2B owners that are likely to be on LinkedIn and will be interested in funding your projects.Other levels of involvement that will be available  include re-seller links to only those who initially contributed in helping me to reach my funding goal. They will be able to resell the eBook or have access to resources attached to the eBook and earn 50% on resales. Other Ways You Can HelpIn the event the funding goal is not reached by the end of November, backers will still have access to their bonuses and I will continue to market the project via my LinkedIn profile page. Therefore, I invite you to join me on LinkedIn and help to share the promotion of the eBook to your connections as well, My LinkedIn address is at: https://www.linkedin.com/in/doherein/
